PY  - 1985
DA  - 1985/09/01/
SN  - 0304-3878
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-3878(85)90036-7
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304387885900367
AB  - Some unintended consequences of financial liberalization in Latin America are analyzed in this paper. Intrinsic imperfections in financial markets, and the policy dilemmas they pose, are reviewed first. The stylized facts of Southern Cone experiments in financial liberation are then presented. Alternative ways of organizing domestic capital markets under Latin American conditions are discussed, and an eclectic, reform mongering program is proposed.
ER  - 

